"1113","svodevelopment1","1.0","LK","individual submissions","social value orientation (TDM); secure attachment (AAS); sample 1","prosocials have a higher level of secure attachment than individualists","only 458 participants in the original paper and 1279 in sample 1 were included in the analysis because of unclassified participants by TDM; number of competitors was very low.","Yi Liu","45049.0","There are more effects in the original and the replication study which are not relevant to the main hypotheses.",NA,"0.114247","0.07974522","573.0","1446.0","Van Lange, P. A. M., De Bruin, E., Otten, W., & Joireman, J. A. (1997). Development of prosocial, individualistic, and competitive orientations: Theory and preliminary evidence. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 73(4), 733–746. https://doi.org/10.1037/0022-3514.73.4.733 Study 1","Liu, Y., Wang, B., & Van Lange, P. A. M. (2022). The Development of Social Value Orientation: Attachment Styles, Number of Siblings, Age, and a Comparison of Measures. European Journal of Personality. Advance online publication. https://doi.org/10.1177/08902070221094216",NA,NA,"0.23","d","0.16","d",NA,NA,NA,NA,"https://osf.io/g9b7c/",NA,"2.0","Mturk","1.0","1.0","1.0",NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,"success","https://osf.io/g9b7c/","2.0","3.0","1.0","1.0","3.0","2.0","3.0","1.0","3.0","3.0","(1) the sample of the study is from the US and UK instead of the Netherlands, thus the language used in the studies is different;(2) some of the measures (e.g., SLM for SVO, AAS and ECR-R for attachment) are not the same as the original study, but we include the measures used in the original study as well; (3) the original Studies 1 and 3 were conducted in paper-and-pencil, while the current studies were conducted online; (4) the replication study has a larger sample size",NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,"Journal of Personality and Social Psychology",NA,NA,NA,NA
